<h2 class="h5 mb-3">Privacy Policy</h2>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="text-muted small">Last updated: April 4, 2026</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">What data we collect</h3>
    <p>When you use Timeframe, we collect and store the following information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information</strong> — your email address, used for authentication.</li>
      <li><strong>Google account data</strong> — when you connect a Google account, we store an OAuth token and your Google email address to access your Google Calendar data.</li>
      <li><strong>Calendar events</strong> — we fetch and store calendar event data (summaries, times, locations) from your connected Google Calendars to display on your devices.</li>
      <li><strong>Device information</strong> — names, model types, and connection details for your registered display devices.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">How we use your data</h3>
    <p>Your data is used solely to render calendar and weather information on your connected e-ink display devices. We do not sell, share, or distribute your data to any third parties.</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">Google API data</h3>
    <p>Timeframe's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements. Calendar data fetched from Google is used exclusively to display events on your devices and is not used for any other purpose.</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">Data retention</h3>
    <p>Calendar event data is retained only as long as needed for display purposes. Past events are automatically cleaned up. Your account data is retained until you delete your account.</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">Data deletion</h3>
    <p>You can delete your account and all associated data at any time from the dashboard. You can also unlink individual Google accounts or delete specific calendars and devices. Deleting your account permanently removes all associated locations, devices, calendars, calendar events, and Google account connections.</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">Self-hosted instances</h3>
    <p>When Timeframe is self-hosted, the operator of the instance is responsible for the security and privacy of all data stored on their server.</p>

    <h3 class="h6 mt-3">Contact</h3>
    <p>For privacy-related questions, please open an issue on the <a href="https://github.com/timeframe/timeframe" target="_blank">Timeframe GitHub repository</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>
